d 'MLM_GOF': module for computing the Goodness-of-fit test after mixed-effects logistic regression with random intercepts
d
d  mlm_gof performs a goodness-of-fit test for binary multilevel
d logistic models fitted by melogit. It extends the grouping-based
d test of Perera, Sooriyarachchi & Wickramasuriya (2016) and
d Fernando & Sooriyarachchi (2022) to models with random
d coefficients (Linden 2026). The test works by dividing
d observations within each level-2 cluster into G groups based on
d their conditional predicted probabilities, then testing whether
d group membership adds explanatory power beyond the fitted model
d via a joint Wald test on G-1 indicator variables. Under a
d well-fitting model, the group indicators should be uninformative
d and the Wald statistic should follow a chi-squared distribution
d with G-1 degrees of freedom. 
d
d KW: mixed-effect logistic regression
d KW: random intercepts
d KW: goodness of fit
d
d Requires: Stata version 11
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260423
d
d Author: Ariel Linden, Linden Consulting Group, LLC
d Support: email alinden@@lindenconsulting.org
d
f mlm_gof.ado
